<h2 id="250">3. Activating the order referrer</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to link items, properties etc. with Mercateo, you have to activate the order referrer Mercateo in the <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the order referrer for Mercateo:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>Mercateo</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="300">4. Setting the variation availability</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to activate all variations that you want to sell on Mercateo. This is done in the <strong>Availability</strong> tab of a variation within the <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open item] » [Open variation]</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Selling all variations of an item on Mercateo</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to sell all variations of an item on Mercateo, carry out the settings below for the item’s main variation. All other variations of the item then inherit the settings of the main variation.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the variation availability for Mercateo:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open item] » [Open variation]</strong>.<br>
→ The tab <strong>Settings</strong> of the variation is shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Availability</strong> area, active the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Markets</strong> area, click in the selection field. <br>
→ A list of all available markets is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Mercateo</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Web API</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The market is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="400">5. Exporting items and item images</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong> menu, you can export your items and item images to Mercateo.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting items:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Export item data</strong>.<br>
→ The item data is exported to Mercateo.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also export item images to Mercateo. A maximum of 500 images can be uploaded at once. Allowed data formats are <strong>JPG</strong>, <strong>PNG</strong>, and <strong>GIF</strong>. No image is uploaded twice.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting item images:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Export 500 item images</strong>.<br>
→ The item images are exported to Mercateo.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">6. Defining a sales price</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Sales prices define the conditions under which a variation is sold at a specific price and on a specific sales channel. That means that to sell variations on {referrer}, you need a sales price in which the order referrer {referrer} is activated. The price that you save for this sales price is the price that will be shown on {referrer}.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining a sales price for {referrer}:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Sales prices » [Open sales price]</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> No sales prices? Then create a <a href="/en/item/settings/prices#100">new sales price</a> first.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>{referrer}</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="600">7. Viewing the export history</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An overview of exported images is displayed in the <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Export history</strong> menu. The images are displayed on different pages. 25 images can be displayed per page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Selecting a page:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Export history</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>page</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to display the page.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The images are displayed along with the corresponding item ID and time of export. It is not possible to export an image more than once. However, if you would like to update an image, e.g. after changes have been made to it, then click on <strong>Delete</strong> in the <strong>Release item image</strong> column. Then export this image again in the <strong>Item images export</strong> area of the <strong>Setup » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
